        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('O/S (Operating System)'); ?>
        <p>An Operating System (<strong>O/S</strong> or <strong>OS</strong>) is a collection of software that manages computer hardware resources and provides common services for computer programs. The operating system is an essential component of the system software in a computer system. Application programs usually require an operating system to function.</p>
        <p>Common Operating systems include <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Windows', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Unix', 'OS'); ?>.</p>
